\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 12. C. pastricensis} Dörfler & Hayek,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  70}: 19 (1921). Robust perennial herb up to 200 cm. Leaves 18-30 × 8-15 cm, pinnatisect, glabrous or ciliate, with 4-7 pairs of lanceolate or oblong, serrate-dentate lobes, the upper lobes decurrent on the midrib. Involucral bracts 5-7 × 4-5 mm, ovate-lanceolate, acute or subacute, purplish-black at apex. Receptacular scales 6-8 × 3-4 mm, spathulate, acuminate, ciliate, glabrous or appressed-pubescent, purplish-black at apex. Corolla c. 14 mm, yellow. Involucel c. 8 mm in fruit, 8-angled, with 4 setae ¼ as long as tube and 4 shorter intermediate setae.{\i  Mountain pastures. • C. Jugoslavia, Albania.} Al Ju.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 13. C. alpina} (L.) Roemer & Schultes,{\i  Syst. Veg.}{\b  3}: 43 (1818). Robust perennial herb up to 200 cm. Leaves 15-42 × 8-18 cm, pinnate or lyrate, pubescent or villous on veins, with 3-8 pairs of oblong-lanceolate, serrate-dentate leaflets, the upper leaflets decurrent, the terminal leaflet often larger than the lateral. Involucral bracts 6-7 × 3·5-4 mm, triangular-lanceolate, acute, sericeous or villous. Receptacular scales 9-12 × 2-3 mm, oblong-spathulate, acuminate, sericeous or villous, with terminal spine. Corolla c. 12 mm, yellow. Involucel 9-12 mm in fruit, 8-angled, with 4 setae c. 1·5 mm and 4 intermediate setae c. 1 mm. •{\i  S.W. & C. Alps, Jura, N. Appennini.} Au Ga He It.
\par 

