\pard\f0\fs28 Stout, biennial herbs, with prickly stems more or less branched above. Leaves opposite, often connate. Capitulum globose to subglobose, ovoid or cylindrical. Involucral bracts in 1-2 rows, linear or lanceolate, erect to patent, with apical spine. Receptacular scales more or less spine-tipped. Involucel more or less 4-angled, united with the ovary below and ending in a short, more or less 4-lobed cup. Calyx cupuliform, ciliate, persistent in fruit. Corolla with a long tube, unequally 4-fid. Achenes 4-angled, appressed-hairy.
